radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: Computed tomography (CT) of the head, cervical spine, abdomen, and pelvis
radiographic_examinations.findings: Stranding of the anterior abdominal wall, subcutaneous tissues of the left flank, and fat of the left retroperitoneum, consistent with soft-tissue contusion or hemorrhage.

radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: CT of the abdomen and pelvis
radiographic_examinations.findings: No renal or ureteral stones, solid renal masses, or ureteral or bladder filling defects. The stranding of the anterior abdominal wall, left flank, and left retroperitoneum appeared to have been stable since the previous study.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Stable since the previous study had been obtained, 3 days earlier.

radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: CT angiography of the head and neck
radiographic_examinations.findings: Normal intracranial and neck vessels, no evidence of intracranial hemorrhage, acute infarction, or intracranial lesions.
